      "content": "i see. sounds like a lot of people see it as a safety thing. but on the other hand, some parents feel like these lessons are actually pretty radical and that it's not the school's job to change how kids view things. do you think there's a way to tell if a curriculum is actually \"inclusive\" versus just being biased toward a certain political viewpoint?",
